This paper deals with mining data streams, which is a topic that falls under the purview of databases (cs.DB) and data structures (cs.DS). The problem of identifying heavy-hitters is a well-studied problem in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the problem of tracking frequent items in a data stream is also relevant to streaming algorithms (cs.SI).
